column11: The tissue lyser was not stopping when expected, so I wasn’t sure if the lysing was for 5 minutes or more. When I stopped it, the timer read 4:36... I don’t know if it completed the 5 minutes and started again. However, the lysing took place until I prep another 12 samples ready for lysing so I am sure the timing was at least 5 minutes

200ul of neat primestore (Primestore Lot:180809 Exp:Aug 2020) was accidentally added to the 460ul transferred into the bashing bead making total volume of 660ul prior to bead beating. After that 260ul was taken and placed in the Qiasympony. Because of the high viscosity of the samples and foaming, 460ul instead of 400ul was taken into the bashing beads. 260ul was introduced into the sarstead tubes to be extracted. The reason for the 60ul increase in both cases is to ensure that at least 400ul and 250 ul are pipetted after some remain in the tube.
